Global Steel Utility Poles Market Insights
Steel Utility Poles Market size was valued at USD 3.5 Billion in 2022 and is projected to reach USD 5.2 Billion by 2030, growing at a CAGR of 5.1% from 2024 to 2030.

Steel Utility Poles Market Overview
The global steel utility poles market is expected to reach a market value of approximately USD 16.2 billion by 2030, growing at a compound annual growth rate (CAGR) of 4.1% from 2023 to 2030. Steel utility poles are widely used in power transmission and distribution infrastructure due to their durability, long lifespan, and ability to withstand harsh weather conditions. The increasing demand for electricity and the ongoing development of electrical grids, particularly in emerging markets, are contributing significantly to the market growth. Steel poles are preferred over wooden poles due to their higher strength and better performance in extreme conditions.

